---
// src/pages/services/range-hood-repair.astro
// Phase 3 Tier 2 (2026-04-28), neutral multi-county hub.
// title/H1/description/phone neutralized to 5 SoCal counties; merged 2-entry LocalBusiness+Service
// schema → single Service entry with inline provider (no address, no geo, no aggregateRating per
// wiki/decisions/nap-rating-policy-ssot.md); areaServed expanded 3 → 5 counties; FAQ + 2 standard
// Qs; Recent Repairs distributed 2 LA + 1 OC + 1 Ventura; high-BTU CFM angle preserved.

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;

const title = "Range Hood Repair, Same-Day Service Across Southern California | Same Day Appliance Repair";
const description = "Range hood repair across LA, OC, Ventura, SB, Riverside. Wolf, Zephyr, Broan, Vent-A-Hood. Wall, under-cabinet, island. BHGS #A49573. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/services/range-hood-repair/";

const faqs = [
  { q: "How much does range hood repair cost?", a: "Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most range hood repairs run between $100 and $280. A fan motor, blower wheel, light socket, or switch replacement is toward the lower end. Control board replacement on premium hoods like Wolf, Zephyr, or Vent-A-Hood runs higher. We provide a written estimate before any work begins. For by-brand cost breakouts see our range hood repair cost page." },
  { q: "Which areas of Southern California do you cover?", a: "All five counties: Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. We dispatch from 8 service territories, West Hollywood (HQ), Los Angeles, Beverly Hills, Pasadena, Thousand Oaks, Irvine, Rancho Cucamonga, and Temecula, so the technician on your call is coming from the closest one. Same-day is our standard." },
  { q: "My range hood fan runs but doesn't seem to clear smoke, is it broken?", a: "Not necessarily. There are two common explanations. First: a clogged grease filter dramatically reduces airflow, a filter that hasn't been cleaned in months can restrict CFM by 50% or more, making the fan seem weak when it's actually working fine. Second: if you have a high-BTU professional range (Wolf, Thermador, BlueStar), your hood may simply be underpowered for the burners. A 30,000 BTU burner on a Wolf requires significantly more CFM than a standard residential hood provides. We assess both when you call." },
  { q: "How often should I clean my range hood filters?", a: "Grease filters should be cleaned every 1–3 months depending on how much you cook. Across SoCal, where people cook at home frequently and often with high-BTU professional ranges, monthly cleaning is not excessive. Most metal mesh filters can go in the dishwasher. Charcoal filters on ductless/recirculating hoods need replacing every 3–6 months, they can't be cleaned, only replaced. A saturated grease filter is both a fire hazard and the most common cause of perceived performance loss." },
  { q: "What is the difference between a vented and ventless range hood?", a: "A vented range hood draws air through a grease filter and exhausts it outside through ductwork, this removes smoke, moisture, heat, and cooking odors from the kitchen entirely. A ventless or recirculating hood draws air through a grease filter and a charcoal filter, then recirculates the cleaned air back into the kitchen, it removes grease and some odors but not moisture or heat. Vented is significantly more effective and preferred for serious cooking. Ventless is the only option in many apartments and condos without ducting." },
  { q: "Do you repair high-end range hoods like Wolf, Vent-A-Hood, and Zephyr?", a: "Yes. Wolf, Vent-A-Hood, Zephyr, Hestan, and Miele are among the premium hood brands we service most across SoCal. These units have different motor assemblies and control systems than consumer-grade hoods. We source OEM parts for Wolf specifically and carry parts for Zephyr and Broan. For Vent-A-Hood and Hestan, parts are sourced from authorized distributors." },
  { q: "My range hood is making a loud noise, what's wrong?", a: "A rattling or vibrating noise often means the blower wheel has accumulated grease buildup and is now unbalanced, or a small object has gotten into the blower housing. A grinding or squealing sound indicates the fan motor bearings are failing. Both are repairable. The blower wheel is a separate component from the motor, we check both before recommending replacement of either." },
  { q: "When does it make sense to repair vs replace a range hood?", a: "Rule of thumb: under 8 years old and the repair is under $250, fix it. Over 12 years old AND repair over $400, consider replacing. Premium hoods (Wolf, Vent-A-Hood, Zephyr Pro, Miele) are almost always worth repairing, they're built for 15-20 year service lives and replacement runs $1,500–$5,000+ before installation. Builder-grade Broan and NuTone hoods have a shorter window. We tell you straight which side of that line your unit falls on." },
  { q: "Is this residential or commercial range hood repair?", a: "This page covers residential range hood repair only, the kind of kitchen ventilation you find in a house, condo, or apartment. For commercial kitchen exhaust hood repair (restaurant, foodservice, Captive-Aire, Halton, Greenheck, Gaylord, UL-300-compliant fire suppression), see our separate commercial exhaust hood page. Different equipment, different scope, different service team." },
  { q: "What does the 90-day warranty cover on range hood repairs?", a: "Every range hood repair we complete carries a 90-day warranty on both parts and labor. If the same issue returns within that window, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave." }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "@id": canonical + "#service",
    "serviceType": "Residential Range Hood Repair",
    "name": "Range Hood Repair, Same Day Appliance Repair",
    "url": canonical,
    "description": "Same-day residential range hood repair across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties, under-cabinet, wall-mounted, island, downdraft, ductless/recirculating, chimney. Wolf, Viking, Thermador, Miele, Jenn-Air, BlueStar, La Cornue, AGA, ILVE, Bertazzoni, Fisher & Paykel, SKS, Fulgor Milano, Gaggenau, Hestan, GE Monogram, Zephyr, Broan, Samsung, LG, GE, Frigidaire, Whirlpool, Maytag. $89 diagnostic, applied toward repair.",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "LocalBusiness",
      "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair",
      "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/",
      "telephone": phone,
      "priceRange": "$$",
      "openingHoursSpecification": [
        {"@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": ["Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday"], "opens": "07:00", "closes": "21:00"},
        {"@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": ["Saturday"], "opens": "08:00", "closes": "19:00"},
        {"@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": ["Sunday"], "opens": "09:00", "closes": "17:00"}
      ]
    },
    "areaServed": [
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Los Angeles County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Orange County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Ventura County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"San Bernardino County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Riverside County"}
    ],
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, applied toward repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Services", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/services/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Range Hood Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
<Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 80px 24px 64px; text-align: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 5px 14px; border-radius: 3px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 20px; max-width: 820px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 1.15rem; color: #ccc; max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto 32px; line-height: 1.6; }
  .cta-row { display: flex; gap: 14px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 16px 34px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-secondary { background: transparent; color: #fff; padding: 16px 34px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.35); }
  .hero-rating { margin-top: 28px; color: #aaa; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .hero-rating strong { color: #fff; }
  .stars { color: #f5b800; margin-right: 6px; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 18px 24px; }
  .trust-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px 32px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 600; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; }
  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-number { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  h2.section-title { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 16px; line-height: 1.2; }
  .section-black h2.section-title { color: #fff; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text); max-width: 720px; }
  .section-black .lead { color: #ccc; }
  .intro-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .intro-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .intro-body p { margin: 0 0 18px; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-box { background: #fff8e7; border: 1px solid #f0d070; border-radius: 8px; padding: 18px 20px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .tip-box .tip-label { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #a07000; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .tip-box p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: #5a4000; margin: 0; line-height: 1.65; }
  .sticky-cta { position: sticky; top: 24px; background: var(--black); border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px 24px; color: #fff; text-align: center; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-label { font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-phone { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; display: block; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .sticky-cta .btn-cta { display: block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px; border-radius: 5px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-sub { font-size: 0.82rem; color: #888; }
  .cta-divider { border: none; border-top: 1px solid #222; margin: 18px 0; }
  .cta-detail { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #aaa; text-align: left; }
  .cta-detail li { margin-bottom: 6px; list-style: none; padding-left: 18px; position: relative; }
  .cta-detail li::before { content: "✓"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--red); font-weight: 700; }
  .type-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(230px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .type-card { background: #111; border: 1px solid #222; border-radius: 8px; padding: 22px 18px; }
  .type-card .type-badge { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 3px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .type-card h3 { font-size: 0.92rem; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 8px; }
  .type-card p { font-size: 0.83rem; color: #888; line-height: 1.55; margin: 0; }
  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 36px; }
  .problem-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 22px 18px; }
  .problem-card h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-card p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
  /* CFM spotlight */
  .cfm-block { background: #100800; border: 1px solid #301800; border-radius: 10px; padding: 34px 30px; margin-top: 36px; }
  .cfm-block .cfm-label { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: #e08030; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .cfm-block h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .cfm-block p { font-size: 0.93rem; color: #c09060; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .cfm-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(180px, 1fr)); gap: 10px; margin-top: 16px; }
  .cfm-item { background: #080400; border: 1px solid #201000; border-radius: 6px; padding: 12px 14px; }
  .cfm-item strong { display: block; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #ffa040; margin-bottom: 3px; }
  .cfm-item span { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #604020; line-height: 1.4; }
  .brands-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .brand-chip { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; padding: 8px 18px; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); }
  .brand-chip.dark { background: #1a1a1a; color: #ddd; border-color: #333; }
  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(255px, 1fr)); gap: 22px; margin-top: 36px; }
  .repair-card { background: #111; border: 1px solid #222; border-radius: 8px; padding: 22px 18px; }
  .repair-card .repair-title { font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 700; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-card h3 { font-size: 0.98rem; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 10px; line-height: 1.3; }
  .repair-card p { font-size: 0.87rem; color: #888; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .repair-card .repair-detail { font-size: 0.78rem; color: #555; border-top: 1px solid #1e1e1e; padding-top: 10px; }
  .pricing-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .price-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 22px 18px; text-align: center; }
  .price-card .price-label { font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .price-card .price-amount { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .price-card .price-desc { font-size: 0.84rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; }
  .price-note { margin-top: 18px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .faq-list { margin-top: 36px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .faq-item h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin: 0 0 10px; }
  .faq-item p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
  .nearby-links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .nearby-links a { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; padding: 8px 16px; font-size: 0.87rem; color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
  .nearby-links a:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 64px 24px; text-align: center; }
  .bottom-cta h2 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .bottom-cta p { color: #aaa; margin: 0 0 32px; font-size: 1.05rem; }
</style>

<!-- HERO + TRUST BAR (unified ServiceHero, neutral defaults) -->
<ServiceHero
  title="Range Hood Repair Across Southern California"
  subtitle="Fan not pulling air, loud blower, lights out, or completely dead, we also tell you if the problem is a dirty filter rather than a broken part before writing a repair order. Same-day across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino & Riverside counties."
  heroImageTitle="Range Hood Repair"
/>

<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01, About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Before we diagnose a broken part, we check the filter.</h2>

        <p>A clogged grease filter is the most common reason a SoCal homeowner calls us about a "broken" range hood, from a Pasadena family kitchen to a Newport Beach panel-ready Wolf to a Thousand Oaks suburban Zephyr to a Riverside Inland-Empire Broan. A filter that hasn't been cleaned in three months can restrict airflow by 50% or more, the fan runs, the motor is fine, but the hood barely pulls air because nothing can get through the filter. We check the filter before concluding anything else is wrong. In many cases that's the whole call.</p>

        <p>The second thing we check for across SoCal kitchens specifically: CFM-to-BTU mismatch. Southern California has more Wolf, Thermador, and BlueStar professional ranges per household than almost anywhere in the country. A Wolf range with 30,000–60,000 BTU burners requires significantly more ventilation capacity than a standard residential range hood provides. When a hood "doesn't seem to work" over a high-BTU professional range, the hood may be functioning correctly, it's just undersized for the job. That's not a repair, it's a replacement or upgrade conversation, and we'll have it honestly.</p>

        <p>When there is an actual mechanical failure, fan motor seized, blower wheel unbalanced with grease buildup, control board failed, lights dead, we carry parts for the brands common across SoCal and can usually complete same-visit.</p>

        <div class="tip-box">
          <div class="tip-label">🧹 Clean Your Filter First</div>
          <p>If your hood seems weak but the fan is running, pull out the metal mesh grease filter and hold it up to the light. If you can't see through it, cleaning it may restore full performance without any repair needed. Most metal filters can go in the dishwasher on the hottest cycle. Charcoal filters on ductless hoods can't be cleaned, they need replacement every 3–6 months. We carry both types.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="sticky-cta">
        <div class="cta-label">Same Day Range Hood Repair</div>
        <a href={phoneHref} class="cta-phone">{phone}</a>
        <a href={phoneHref} class="btn-cta">Call Now, We Pick Up</a>
        <a href="/book" class="btn-cta" style="background:#222; margin-top:-4px;">Book Online</a>
        <div class="cta-sub">Mon–Fri 7am–9pm · Sat 8am–7pm · Sun 9am–5pm</div>
        <hr class="cta-divider" />
        <ul class="cta-detail">
          <li>$89 diagnostic, applied to repair</li>
          <li>90-day warranty on parts &amp; labor</li>
          <li>Filter + CFM assessment included</li>
          <li>Wolf, Vent-A-Hood, Zephyr, Broan</li>
          <li>BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410, · Insured</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- HOOD TYPES -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, Hood Types We Service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every range hood configuration in SoCal kitchens</h2>
    <p class="lead">Mounting style, venting type, and brand all affect how we diagnose and access the unit. We come prepared for each configuration.</p>

    <div class="type-grid">
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-badge">Under-Cabinet</div>
        <h3>Under-Cabinet Hoods</h3>
        <p>Most common in standard kitchens and apartments. Mounted beneath upper cabinets. Usually vented through the cabinet above or directly through the wall. Common in SoCal's older housing stock and renovated condos.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-badge">Wall-Mounted</div>
        <h3>Wall-Mounted Chimney Hoods</h3>
        <p>Decorative stainless or custom-panel chimney hoods mounted on the wall above the range. Popular in renovated kitchens across Westside LA. Higher-end models from Zephyr, Vent-A-Hood, Hestan, and Wolf.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-badge">Island</div>
        <h3>Island / Ceiling Hoods</h3>
        <p>Suspended from the ceiling over an island or peninsula cooktop. Require ceiling duct routing. Common in open-plan LA kitchens with island cooktops. Generally higher CFM requirements than wall-mounted units.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-badge">Insert</div>
        <h3>Insert / Built-In Hoods</h3>
        <p>The ventilation unit is concealed inside custom cabinetry, only the grille and controls are visible. Common in high-end kitchens where the hood is integrated into the cabinetry design. Brands: Wolf, Miele, Thermador, Best.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-badge">Vented</div>
        <h3>Vented (Ducted) Hoods</h3>
        <p>Exhausts air to the exterior through ductwork. Far more effective than recirculating, removes smoke, moisture, heat, and odors entirely. Required for high-BTU professional ranges. The correct choice for serious cooking.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-badge">Ventless</div>
        <h3>Ventless / Recirculating Hoods</h3>
        <p>Filters air through grease and charcoal filters, then returns it to the kitchen. The only option in many apartments without duct access. Charcoal filters must be replaced every 3–6 months, not cleanable. We carry replacements.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PROBLEMS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03, Common Problems</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What our technicians fix most often</h2>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>Fan Not Working / No Suction</h3>
        <p>Check the grease filter first, a saturated filter can reduce airflow dramatically. If the filter is clean and the fan still doesn't pull air, the fan motor has failed. On multi-speed hoods, individual speed settings can fail independently, one speed works, others don't.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>Loud Rattling or Vibration</h3>
        <p>A blower wheel caked with grease becomes unbalanced and vibrates the entire hood. Cleaning the blower wheel, a separate component from the motor, often resolves the noise without replacing anything. If noise persists after cleaning, the motor bearings are failing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>Grinding or Squealing Noise</h3>
        <p>Fan motor bearing failure. The motor continues to run but with increasing noise as the bearings degrade. Left unaddressed, the motor eventually seizes. We carry replacement motors for the major brands we service most across SoCal.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>Lights Not Working</h3>
        <p>Usually a burned-out bulb, a failed light socket, or a loose wiring connection. On LED range hoods with integrated lighting, the LED board itself can fail. We carry replacement bulbs and sockets for the common brands. LED board replacement on premium hoods requires sourcing OEM components.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>Control Panel / Buttons Not Responding</h3>
        <p>A failed control board or a membrane switch panel that's degraded. On touchscreen hoods (Zephyr, Broan Elite), the capacitive touch layer can fail. We test the switch panel and wiring before recommending a full board replacement, which is more expensive.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>Hood Completely Dead</h3>
        <p>Check the circuit breaker first, range hoods are often on a dedicated circuit. A blown thermal fuse inside the hood (triggered by excessive grease buildup causing heat) can also cut all power. A completely dead hood on an intact circuit usually has a failed control board or power supply component.</p>
      </div>
