<!-- MATCHED-RANGE INTEGRATION -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">05c, Matched-Range Integration</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Hood and range are often one coordinated system</h2>
    <p class="lead">On most luxury installs the hood is not a standalone appliance, it's coordinated to the range below it, by the same manufacturer, with shared control logic. That affects both what breaks and how we diagnose.</p>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>Auto-coupling (Miele Con@ctivity, Samsung SmartThings, LG ThinQ, SKS)</h3>
        <p>Modern luxury brands couple hood speed to range burner use via Bluetooth or WiFi. When the "hood doesn't auto-start with the range anymore" call comes in, the first check is firmware and pairing, often a reset fixes it without any hardware replacement. When firmware isn't the issue, it's the pairing module on either the hood or the range side.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>Sub-Zero Group coordinated parts (Wolf + Sub-Zero + Cove)</h3>
        <p>Wolf hood + Wolf range + Sub-Zero refrigeration routes through the same Sub-Zero Group Madison WI factory parts chain. When a Wolf hood part doesn't have stock, sometimes a Sub-Zero Group technician update lists a cross-reference part with stock, we check before telling a customer we can't source.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>BSH family (Thermador + Bosch + Gaggenau)</h3>
        <p>Thermador, Bosch, and Gaggenau all route through BSH Irvine CA for US parts, so LA is effectively LA-local parts for all three. Some motor and LED components share across Bosch and entry-Thermador hoods; Gaggenau 400 Series Vario modular parts are brand-specific and don't cross-fit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>Whirlpool-family (Whirlpool + Maytag + KitchenAid + Jenn-Air)</h3>
        <p>Four brand names, one parts chain through Whirlpool's Benton Harbor MI network. A Maytag hood part number and a Whirlpool equivalent will often be the same physical part with different labels, useful when one has stock and the other doesn't. Jenn-Air downdraft mechanisms are the exception, brand-specific parts with longer lead times.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>Haier-family (GE + GE Profile + GE Cafe + GE Monogram)</h3>
        <p>The GE tier hierarchy (mass-market → Profile premium → Cafe customizable → Monogram ultra-luxury) all routes through GE Appliances Louisville KY under Haier parentage. Different series use different control platforms, Monogram Statement Collection has brand-specific parts; Cafe and Profile share more.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <h3>LG-family (LG + LG Studio + Signature Kitchen Suite)</h3>
        <p>LG's three-tier residential stack, LG mass-market, LG Studio premium, SKS ultra-luxury, all manufactured in Huntsville AL since 2019. Motor and LED components share across the tiers; control-board firmware and aesthetic trim are tier-specific. SKS-labeled parts are distinct from LG Studio equivalents.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

