<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">08, Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Range hood repair, what people ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does range hood repair cost?</h3>
        <p>Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most repairs run between $100 and $280. Fan motor, blower wheel, light socket, or switch replacement is toward the lower end. Control board replacement on premium hoods runs higher. We provide a written estimate before any work begins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Which areas of Southern California do you cover?</h3>
        <p>All five counties: Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. We dispatch from 8 service territories so the technician on your call is coming from the closest one. Same-day is our standard.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My range hood fan runs but doesn't clear smoke, is it broken?</h3>
        <p>Check the grease filter first. A clogged filter can restrict airflow by 50%+, the fan runs but nothing gets through. If you have a high-BTU professional range, the hood may also be undersized for the burners. We assess both before recommending any parts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How often should I clean my range hood filters?</h3>
        <p>Metal mesh grease filters every 1–3 months, monthly if you cook frequently or use high-BTU burners. Most can go in the dishwasher. Charcoal filters on ductless hoods every 3–6 months, they can't be cleaned, only replaced. A saturated grease filter is both a fire hazard and the most common cause of performance loss.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is the difference between a vented and ventless range hood?</h3>
        <p>Vented hoods exhaust air outside through ductwork, removing smoke, moisture, heat, and odors entirely. Ventless/recirculating hoods filter and return air to the kitchen, they remove grease and some odors but not moisture or heat. Vented is significantly more effective. Ventless is the only option in apartments without duct access.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair Wolf, Vent-A-Hood, and Zephyr range hoods?</h3>
        <p>Yes. These are among the premium hood brands we service most across SoCal. We source OEM parts for Wolf specifically and carry parts for Zephyr and Broan. For Vent-A-Hood and Hestan, parts are sourced from authorized distributors.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My range hood is making a loud noise, what's wrong?</h3>
        <p>Rattling or vibration usually means the blower wheel has grease buildup and is unbalanced. Grinding or squealing means the fan motor bearings are failing. We check the blower wheel before the motor, cleaning it often resolves the noise without needing a motor replacement.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>When does it make sense to repair vs replace a range hood?</h3>
        <p>Rule of thumb: under 8 years old and the repair is under $250, fix it. Over 12 years old AND repair over $400, consider replacing. Premium hoods (Wolf, Vent-A-Hood, Zephyr Pro, Miele) are almost always worth repairing, they're built for 15-20 year service lives and replacement runs $1,500–$5,000+ before installation. Builder-grade Broan and NuTone hoods have a shorter window. We tell you straight which side of that line your unit falls on.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What does the 90-day warranty cover on range hood repairs?</h3>
        <p>Every range hood repair we complete carries a 90-day warranty on both parts and labor. If the same issue returns within that window, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- COMMERCIAL DISAMBIG + PRICE-LIST -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">08a, Scope &amp; Pricing</p>
